  note         = {Exact 2018/2021/2022/2024 survey-weighted HOMOSEX values are ACCOUNT-GATED on the Data Explorer (UNVERIFIED at primary), but the DIRECTION is corroborated: ``always wrong'' = 34.9\% in 2024 (-> ``not wrong at all'' mid-50s), and Gallup's parallel moral-acceptance measure fell 71\%->~64\% (2022->23). DISCOVERY/CAVEAT: the GSS moved to mixed-mode collection beginning with the 2021 wave (pandemic); the 2021 wave used push-to-web (response rate ~17\% vs ~50\% in 2022), which tends to RAISE ``not wrong at all'' --- so a 2021--22 peak may be partly a mode artifact. NORC cautions against reading post-2020 changes as pure attitude shifts. Reconcile the manuscript's ~63\% (2022) with the brief's ~61\% (2022).},
